ygData.subject: RE: Missed Notes
ygData.msgSnippet: Oh sorry, thought I gave you numbers, I tried to use Denons 30 times and missed notes everytime. It never fired. Are those good enough? ... From: John
ygData.messageBody:
Oh sorry, thought I gave you numbers, I tried to use Denons 30 times and
missed notes everytime. It never fired. Are those good enough?

-----Original Message-----
From: John Robertson [mailto:johnr@...]
Sent: Wednesday, August 11, 1999 1:11 PM
To: eqbards@onelist.com
Subject: Re: [eqbards] Missed Notes


From: John Robertson <johnr@...>



"Chris Kuenster (Entex)" wrote:

> From: "Chris Kuenster (Entex)" <v-ntxck@...>
>
> As I said, my skills are all at or above 190, and approaching 200. My
> regrets that your Brass skills are poor, perhaps a little practice is in
> order. I have tested this and as I said several times I am missing notes
on
> songs I NEVER missed notes on before.

It's hard to have sympathy for you, when you turn a suggested explanation
into
an irrelevant attack on my brass skills. If you've done testing, then show
us
the numbers. So far everyone who has posted numbers, as far as I can tell,
is
showing perfectly reasonable missed note rates. If you have evidence to the
contrary, if anyone does, we can start to reasonably believe there's a
difference, but most people seem to not be experiencing what you are.

I don't think it is server specific, btw, since John Kim, who also says his
missed note rates are up, is on the same server as I am, and I haven't
experienced it.

Jyzan
